"{\"uid\": \"thetablet.org-paris-olympic-committee-makes-soft-apology-for-last-supper-drag-parody\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"By Elise Ann Allen  ROME (Crux) - Representatives of the Paris 2024 Olympics Committee have apologized to anyone offended by a drag parody of the Last Supper during the opening ceremony, insisting that their intention was to foster inclusion and celebrate diversity.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_L._Allen\", \"score\": 0.9999999758160815, \"rank\": 2.4183871678946255e-08, \"text\": \"Allen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_L._Allen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_L._Allen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 spokesperson Anne Descamps was asked about the outcry during an International Olympic Committee news conference Sunday, saying in response, \\\"Clearly there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group.\\\"\", \"from\": 268, \"to\": 500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 268, \"end\": 278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.214857437949346e-14, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 297, \"end\": 305, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}, {\"begin\": 343, \"end\": 374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"On the contrary, I think (with) Thomas Jolly, we really did try to celebrate community tolerance,\\\" she said, adding, \\\"Looking at the result of the polls that we shared, we believe that this ambition was achieved.\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If people have taken any offense, we are, of course, really, really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly, the ceremony's artistic director, in his own remarks to theAssociated Pressabout the event, said it was meant to celebrate diversity and pay tribute to feasting and French gastronomy.\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 965, \"end\": 971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999993153867378, \"rank\": 6.84323859019513e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My wish is not to be subversive, nor to mock or to shock,\\\" he said, saying, \\\"Most of all, I wanted to send a message of love, a message of inclusion and not at all to divide.\\\"\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 1161, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The apology was made in response to a wave of backlash from Catholics, members of other Christian communities, atheists, and members of other faith groups to the July 26 opening ceremony for the Paris Olympics, which featured a group of scantily clad men in drag dancing provocatively while parodying the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 1163, \"to\": 1480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1223, \"end\": 1232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.297332701801895e-16, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1251, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999770227179862, \"rank\": 2.2977809783723543e-05, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At one point, the genitalia of a man wearing short black hotpants was exposed while a little girl stood in front of him, in front of what was supposed to be the table.\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1649, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Catholic leaders from around the world, including the French bishops conference and two Vatican officials, condemned the performance, with at least one, Archbishop Charles Scicluna of Malta and adjunct secretary of the Vatican's Dicastery for the Doctrine of the Faith, making a formal complaint to the French ambassador to Malta, encouraging others to do the same.\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1651, \"end\": 1659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.855129898514226e-12, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1705, \"end\": 1711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999993153867378, \"rank\": 6.84323859019513e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.8216298681008182, \"rank\": 0.13985046802135578, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 1815, \"end\": 1831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charles Scicluna\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Scicluna\"}, {\"begin\": 1835, \"end\": 1840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"score\": 0.9999999974647835, \"rank\": 2.5265576427007346e-09, \"text\": \"Malta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\"}, {\"begin\": 1954, \"end\": 1960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999993153867378, \"rank\": 6.84323859019513e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1975, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"score\": 0.9999999974647835, \"rank\": 2.5265576427007346e-09, \"text\": \"Malta\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some commentators in the wake of the controversy have claimed that the performance was evocative of the feast of Dionysus, rather than the Last Supper, as a nod to the Greek roots of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2131, \"end\": 2139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7573697739386115e-30, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 2186, \"end\": 2191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.9993840963939215, \"rank\": 0.0006132836674941719, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the artists who participated in the parody have confirmed in online social media posts and in comments to the press that the performance was, in fact, intended to imitate Leonardo da Vinci's famed painting of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2401, \"end\": 2418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6859705879503314e-28, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French drag queen and rapper Piche from the show Drag Race France spoke to French media, saying the intention was to create a tableau of the Last Supper in the pouring rain.\", \"from\": 2457, \"to\": 2630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2457, \"end\": 2463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999993153867378, \"rank\": 6.84323859019513e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2506, \"end\": 2522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drag_Race_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Drag Race France\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drag_Race_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Drag_Race_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2532, \"end\": 2538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999993153867378, \"rank\": 6.84323859019513e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I received a lot of messages of support and people who were very happy that I was there and very surprised that there were drag queens at the opening ceremony,\\\" he said, adding that the opposition to the performance indicates that \\\"we have succeeded and we have done what had to be done, that we have been fair and representative.\\\"\", \"from\": 2632, \"to\": 2964, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Art always divides.\", \"from\": 2966, \"to\": 2986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As long as it does not move people, it's not art for me,\\\" he said, saying the depiction of the Last Supper \\\"is not a provocation.\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 3116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a biblical representation that has been reused in pop culture for decades and it's never really been a problem.\\\"\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There were no real provocations or anything that was truly obscene.\", \"from\": 3236, \"to\": 3304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We did not make fun of the painting at all \\u2026 it's really just because it's queers and drag queens who use that representation that it bothers,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3305, \"to\": 3457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly, Barbara Butch, a lesbian who donned a silver headdress and low-cut dress while portraying the figure of Jesus in the Last Supper parody, said the opening ceremony was intended to bring people together.\", \"from\": 3459, \"to\": 3671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3470, \"end\": 3483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}, {\"begin\": 3574, \"end\": 3579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999997644409, \"rank\": 2.3559296506354007e-10, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to her Instagram profile, Butch is \\\"a Love activist, DJ and producer based in Paris.\", \"from\": 3673, \"to\": 3767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3690, \"end\": 3699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.913253838139809e-39, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}, {\"begin\": 3761, \"end\": 3766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.071230202005683e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My aim is to unite people, gather humans & share love through music for all of Us to dance & make our hearts beat (in unison)!\", \"from\": 3768, \"to\": 3894, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Music sounds better with all of Us!\\\"\", \"from\": 3895, \"to\": 3931, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Butch posted an image of the drag parody of the Last Supper above an image of Da Vinci's original painting to her Instagram account with the comment, \\\"Oh yes!\", \"from\": 3933, \"to\": 4091, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4011, \"end\": 4019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.926333653570847e-32, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 4047, \"end\": 4056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.913253838139809e-39, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Oh yes!\", \"from\": 4092, \"to\": 4099, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new gay testament!\\\"\", \"from\": 4100, \"to\": 4123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The post was subsequently deleted.\", \"from\": 4124, \"to\": 4158, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the Olympic Committee's apology, many Catholic leaders and commentators have said it does not go far enough and fails to make amends for the offense given to the world's 2.6 billion Christians.\", \"from\": 4160, \"to\": 4361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4206, \"end\": 4214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.855129898514226e-12, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 4350, \"end\": 4360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9723672467228136, \"rank\": 0.028085276990019867, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a July 28 video published on social media platform X, previously known as Twitter, Bishop Robert Barron of Winona-Rochester, Minnesota, founder of the popular Word on Fire ministry, which is a benefactor ofCrux, criticized the apology.\", \"from\": 4363, \"to\": 4601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4440, \"end\": 4447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7287899518756195e-26, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}, {\"begin\": 4456, \"end\": 4469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.831331330172336e-36, \"text\": \"Robert Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\"}, {\"begin\": 4473, \"end\": 4489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Catholic_Diocese_of_Winona\\u2013Rochester\", \"score\": 0.9892654137746267, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Winona-Rochester\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Catholic_Diocese_of_Winona\\u2013Rochester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Catholic_Diocese_of_Winona\\u2013Rochester\"}, {\"begin\": 4491, \"end\": 4500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.9999987885783473, \"rank\": 1.2113915258674859e-06, \"text\": \"Minnesota\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bishop Barron, who had previously published a video condemning the Last Supper parody, said Descamps' words were \\\"anything but an apology.\\\"\", \"from\": 4603, \"to\": 4742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4603, \"end\": 4609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9998763467333729, \"rank\": 0.0001236685585754081, \"text\": \"Bishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\"}, {\"begin\": 4610, \"end\": 4616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.462700256646377e-19, \"text\": \"Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 4695, \"end\": 4703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In fact, it's kind of a masterpiece of woke duplicity \\u2026 If they felt this is meant to mollify Christians, I would think again,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 4744, \"to\": 4881, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4839, \"end\": 4849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9723672467228136, \"rank\": 0.028085276990019867, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pointing to Descamps's assertion that they did not intend to offend any religious group, Bishop Barron said, \\\"Give me a break.\\\"\", \"from\": 4883, \"to\": 5010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4895, \"end\": 4903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}, {\"begin\": 4972, \"end\": 4978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9998763467333729, \"rank\": 0.0001236685585754081, \"text\": \"Bishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\"}, {\"begin\": 4979, \"end\": 4985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.462700256646377e-19, \"text\": \"Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have a group of drag queens cavorting in a sexually provocative way, clearly in imitation of Da Vinci's Last Supper, which presents to the world the Last Supper of Jesus, and no disrespect was meant?\", \"from\": 5012, \"to\": 5215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5109, \"end\": 5117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.926333653570847e-32, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 5180, \"end\": 5185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999997644409, \"rank\": 2.3559296506354007e-10, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do you think anyone takes that seriously?\\\"\", \"from\": 5216, \"to\": 5258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"he said.\", \"from\": 5259, \"to\": 5267, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He also took issue with the statement that the intention was to celebrate community and tolerance, saying there is tolerance \\\"except for those pesky 2.6 billion Christians on the planet.\\\"\", \"from\": 5269, \"to\": 5456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5430, \"end\": 5440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9723672467228136, \"rank\": 0.028085276990019867, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everyone's welcome, everyone's tolerated, all this lovely diversity, until you get to anyone that disagrees with your ideology, like these 2.6 billion people.\", \"from\": 5458, \"to\": 5617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So do not give me this business about tolerance and diversity,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 5618, \"to\": 5690, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Referring to Descamps's statement that their goal of celebrating tolerance was achieved, Bishop Barron asked rhetorically, \\\"I wonder what planet they are living on if they think that harmony and peace and all this was achieved by this clear affront to Christians.\\\"\", \"from\": 5692, \"to\": 5956, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5705, \"end\": 5713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}, {\"begin\": 5781, \"end\": 5787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9998763467333729, \"rank\": 0.0001236685585754081, \"text\": \"Bishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\"}, {\"begin\": 5788, \"end\": 5794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.462700256646377e-19, \"text\": \"Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 5944, \"end\": 5954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9723672467228136, \"rank\": 0.028085276990019867, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bishop Barron also condemned the wording of the apology as condescending, saying the tone does not read apologetic, but rather says, \\\"If you are so simple-minded and stupid to have been offended by this wonderful expression of French culture, well, we are sorry about that.\\\"\", \"from\": 5958, \"to\": 6232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5958, \"end\": 5964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9998763467333729, \"rank\": 0.0001236685585754081, \"text\": \"Bishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\"}, {\"begin\": 5965, \"end\": 5971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.462700256646377e-19, \"text\": \"Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 6185, \"end\": 6199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Christians were offended because it was offensive.\", \"from\": 6234, \"to\": 6285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6235, \"end\": 6245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9723672467228136, \"rank\": 0.028085276990019867, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it was intended to be offensive.\", \"from\": 6286, \"to\": 6322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So please do not patronize us with this condescending remark of, 'Well, if you had any bad feelings, we are awfully sorry about that,'\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 6323, \"to\": 6467, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This apology will do little to satisfy Christians who were offended by the performance, he said, saying, \\\"A real apology would be something like, 'this was a mistake, it should never have been done, we are sorry for it.'\\\"\", \"from\": 6469, \"to\": 6690, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6508, \"end\": 6518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9723672467228136, \"rank\": 0.028085276990019867, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not think Christians should be mollified, I think we should keep raising our voices,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 6692, \"to\": 6792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6708, \"end\": 6718, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9723672467228136, \"rank\": 0.028085276990019867, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Username or Email  Password  Remember Me          Your email will be used to send you The Tablet newsletter.\", \"from\": 6794, \"to\": 6902, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6880, \"end\": 6890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Tablet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.098874987013776e-46, \"text\": \"The Tablet\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Tablet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Tablet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time using the link in our emails.\", \"from\": 6903, \"to\": 6964, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more details, review our privacy policy.More info.\", \"from\": 6965, \"to\": 7019, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do you have a photo or video you want to share with The Tablet?\", \"from\": 7027, \"to\": 7090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7079, \"end\": 7089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Tablet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.098874987013776e-46, \"text\": \"The Tablet\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Tablet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Tablet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Click here to send it straight to our news desk.\", \"from\": 7091, \"to\": 7139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You